Add XWin server (or Cygwin bash shell) to start menu:
  Copy (not Right-drag) it there from the Start Menu (it's in "All Programs > Cygwin-X"), OR In start menu, right-click on cygwin xterm and then do "pin to start menu".  Don't put it on the desktop.
  Rename it to "xterm".
  The terminal window starts really small; I should see about fixing that.
Add XLaunch to the desktop.  It's for use if xterm doesn't work.  XLaunch does
  work, but requires going through multple screens rather than just clicking
  on the icon.
Not needed: cygwin terminal, xterm

Test that openssh was downloaded:
     ssh mernst@godwit.cs.washington.edu

